We get an access violation from CoreCLR, which causes w3wp.exe or dotnet.exe to crash (depending on selected hostingmodel).

We call the following piece of code on IIS / ASP.NET Core 2.2.3. It will _randomly_ fail on IIS but running the code locally in a console program does not produce any problems with the exact same input strings:

```
        public static string Encrypt(string inputText, string password)
        {
            keyGenerator = new Rfc2898DeriveBytes(password, Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(password));

            // error will occur here:
